The Florida Department of Law Enforcement issued an Amber Alert on Thursday morning for an 11-year-old girl who may be in the company of a 42-year-old man. The girl’s name is Banesa Fernandez-Santis. She is a white-Hispanic girl who stands 5 feet 2 inches tall, weighs 120 pounds and has black hair and brown eyes. She also has scars on her face, the FDLE said. She was last seen in the area of the 5600 block of Arthur Brown Road in Walnut Hill, which is in Escambia County in the Florida Panhandle. The FDLE said Banesa may be in the company of Brijido Manriquez-Ortis, a white-Hispanic man who stands 5 feet 8inches tall, weighs 140 pounds and has black hair and brown eyes. Anyone with information on the girl’s whereabouts can contact the Escambia County Sheriff’s Office at (850)-436-9620 or 911.